chunk_content: Within these domains, and given the needs of the government and the availability of funds and timing, additional strata can be sampled if required, including: • By facility type or facilities with paper versus electronic patient monitoring records; • Of particular programmatic importance: for example, 2 or 3 districts might be oversampled to meet the particular needs of a partner or meets the concerns of the Ministry of Health; and • To measure the reporting adjustments at the subnational level (recommended for the second phase of DQA). 219 This should be balanced against the sample size implications of increasing the number of strata. In implementing the sampling approach, the following steps are followed. A I. Create a sampling frame: a list of all ART sites nationally. In the second phase of DQA, countries may consider P disaggregating this list by subnational unit (such as region or district). The sample frame should include the P following information: E N a.
